The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Driver held
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Driver held
                            
	Calcutta, April 5: The bus driver, Swapan Sarkar, 42, was arrested tonight near his home in Mullickpara, Dum Dum. He had jumped off the bus before it toppled over into the canal and had been in hiding since, police said.         
	The families of each of the dead will receive Rs 1.25 lakh  Rs 50,000 from the state government, Rs 25,000 from the Rajarhat and Gopalpur municipality, and Rs 25,000 each from the local area development funds of MLA Robin Mondal and MP Amitava Nandi. No compensation has yet been announced for the injured.                                                                                                                                           
